abstract: "Inalpha is an open-source quant agent framework that brings engineering discipline to LLM-driven trading. It features a factor lab, risk engine, strategy evolution, and audit-grade plan/exec with hooks, scoped permissions, and signed audit trails — inspired by Claude Code's engineering patterns and NautilusTrader's unified backtest=paper=live kernel."
keywords:
  - "quantitative trading"
  - "agent framework"
  - "LLM orchestration"
  - "factor research"
  - "backtesting"
  - "algorithmic trading"
  - "hooks"
  - "permissions"
  - "plan-exec"
  - "audit trail"
